children.text: The stair treads do not appear to contain any non-slip finish to them.
Part 3.9.1.4 Slip-resistance of the National Construction Code’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that
a surface with a slip-resistance classification not less than that listed in Table 3.9.1.3 when tested in accordance with AS 4586; or
a nosing strip with a slip-resistance classification not less than that listed in Table 3.9.1.3 when tested in accordance with AS 4586’ .
The finish of these treads must be either confirmed as complying with this requirement of the Building Code of Australia (BCA) or otherwise made to do so.
